LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 18
BY BUSINESS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO THE IDAHO BUILDING CODE ACT; AMENDING CHAPTER 41, TITLE 39, IDAHO
3 CODE, BY THE ADDITION OF A NEW SECTION 39-4109B, IDAHO CODE, TO PROHIBIT
4 CERTAIN ELECTRIC VEHICLE BUILDING PLAN REQUIREMENTS AND TO PROVIDE FOR
5 PREEMPTION; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Chapter 41, Title 39, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
8 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
9 ignated as Section 39-4109B, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
10 39-4109B. ELECTRIC VEHICLE BUILDING PLAN REQUIREMENTS -- PREEMP-
11 TION. (1) Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary,
12 neither the state of Idaho nor any local government in Idaho shall adopt any
13 requirement that an electric vehicle (EV) charging station or a designated
14 EV parking space be included in a building plan.
15 (2) This section supersedes any local laws, ordinances, orders, rules,
16 or regulations enacted by a political subdivision or municipality that re-
17 quires an EV charging station or a designated EV parking space to be included
18 in a building plan.
19 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after its
21 passage and approval.

